Microsoft Corp Partners Tata Consultancy Services Ltd and Wipro Ltd For CityNext Initiative - Business Standard
Wednesday, 20 Nov 2013 06:01am EST
Business Standard reported that Microsoft Corp has tied up with Tata Consultancy Services Ltd and Wipro Ltd to launch its CityNext initiative to leverage technology for sustainable growth of cities in India. The initiative will work on 40 areas in eight domains -- Energy & water, infrastructure, planning & buildings, Transportation, Public safety & justice, Tourism, recreation & culture, Education, Health and Social services & government administration. Microsoft said in a statement that these areas will help address 90% of the challenges cities face, and CityNext will address them through its partner network of more than 430,000 technology experts across the globe.Â 
